<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Version>0.6.5.2</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.5.2</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.5.2</FileVersion>
    <Authors>LastOnionKnight</Authors>
    <Description>Tonberry Tactics — companion web app for the in-game plugin. AskMrRobot-style hybrid gear optimizer for FFXIV. Pure-Math by default, Balance preset queued, exports plans back to the plugin via GG-PLAN:v1: strings. v0.6.5.2 ("Release Hardening") teaches release.ps1 to (a) fetch + rebase before staging so accumulated upstream commits no longer cause the final git push to be rejected as non-fast-forward, and (b) gate the release on a successful dotnet build (symmetric with Core and Plugin, which have had build gates since v0.4.6 — Web previously lacked one, which is why the v0.6.5.1 first attempt shipped a broken csproj commit + tag to GitHub before being force-pushed back). Also wraps the EVERCOLD wordmark in an external link to the official FFXIV expansion page. No application-logic changes. v0.6.5.1 ("Audit reads right") was the hotfix for the off-by-one Tier display bug introduced in v0.6.5: wire format's Grade field is 0-indexed (Tier XII materia arrives as Grade=11) but the audit was comparing against MateriaTiers.CurrentCapTier (=12, 1-indexed) and feeding the raw 0-indexed value to RomanGrade. Result: every Tier XII meld rendered as "XI" and tripped the under-tier flag with a phantom upgrade recommendation. A fully-melded set produced 20 phantom findings. Fix adds 1 to Grade at the consumer (Index.razor BuildAuditFindings) so the wire format stays unchanged. Pairs with plugin v0.6.5.1 ("Quiet Info") which fixes a latent /ttinfo hard-crash.</Description>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/TonberryTactics</RepositoryUrl>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly" Version="10.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.DevServer" Version="10.0.0" PrivateAssets="all" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
